Oops, there is a bug here.  This should be:

``` java
boolean success = false;
try {
  super.close();
  success = true;
} finally {
  try {
    getAndRethrow(mCopyFuture);
  } catch (IOException e) {
    if (success) {
      throw e;
    }
  }
}
```

I could probably rework this to have the `Closeable` interface as well, allowing me to use `Util.closeQuietly`

